The paper proposes a technique for unsupervised learning using deep convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of clustering algorithms is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on natural language processing (cs.CL) by improving the ability to train deep neural networks with smaller amounts of labeled data.
